	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002243_0001"/><!--pb/@n='65r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right">31 March 1865</p><!--printed letterhead--><!--
<p rend="right">NEWSTEAD ABBEY</p>
<p rend="right">MANSFIELD</p>
<p rend="right">NOTTS</p>
--><!--printed letterhead ends here-->
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
				<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/>I have been thinking 
<lb/>it might be well to take 
<lb/>all about the Oxford 
<lb/>and Cambridge Mission 
<lb/>and put it into one 
<lb/>chapter and Head it 
<lb/>O &amp; C. Mission &amp;c<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>Would that be better 
<lb/>than having it 
<lb/>mixed up as it 
<lb/>now is. I have 
<lb/>given <persName>Bishop 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002243_0002"/><!--pb/@n='65v'-->
<lb/>Mackenzie</persName> high com
<lb/>mendation for 
<lb/>goodness of heart 
<lb/>&amp; earnest devotion 
<lb/>to his work as I think 
<lb/>he deserves it, but 
<lb/>I am at a loss what to 
<lb/>say about <persName>Tozer</persName><reg>.</reg>
<lb/>It won<reg>'</reg>t do to say 
<lb/>he is a good pious 
<lb/>donkey. I am at the 
<lb/>conclusion now 
<lb/>a sort of recounting 
<lb/>of results and telling 
<lb/>what I think about 
<lb/>Missions squadron &amp;c<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002243_0003"/><!--pb/@n='66r'-->
<lb/>I think the frontispiece 
<lb/>very good. If the 
<lb/>3<hi rend="sup">d</hi> crack were 
<lb/>drawn a little more 
<lb/>to the right it would 
<lb/>be better. <persName>Baines</persName>
<lb/>certainly did not 
<lb/>go over there - </p>
<lb/><p>When you have 
<lb/>done with the 
<lb/>paintings I shall 
<lb/>write a note of 
<lb/>thanks to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Layard</persName><reg>.</reg>
<lb/>It was from his 
<lb/>order that I got 
<lb/>them from A.G.S.</p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002243_0004"/><!--pb/@n='66v'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> &amp; M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> Webb</persName> are now 
<lb/>in London for advice 
<lb/>about his knee <placeName>51 Upper 
<lb/>Brook St</placeName><reg>.</reg></p>
			
</div>
